Updated review: They've changed their menu slightly -- whole/half chickens are back, along with free bread and 1 free sauce. The downside is that now it's $11.25 instead of the $10 it used to be before the renovation. It's still better than the previous menu (no free bread or sauce).  There’s still no small sides available outside of lunch hours. Half chicken + one side is at minimum $19.25 (over $21 if you prefer mac-n-cheese). Haven’t been back since my initial review...can’t comment on quality. ===================== Original review: Been here alot over the last year or so and things have been good up to recently. Their prices used to be a little bit steep, but the quality across the board was good enough to justify it.  Recently, they changed their menu and raised the prices further. No more free bread with your order, sauces went from $0.50 to $2.00 (!!), no option to order small sides outside of lunch hours,  "large" sides are the same size as they used to be, but now come with a price hike.  Quality is still good, but the half/whole chicken model was perfectly fine...not sure why they got rid of it. If anything just add the side of chicken breast and chicken thigh along with the half/whole chicken.  I really liked this place but I think I'm going to stay away for the time being. I can't justify $18 for a small order of chicken thighs with a side of mac and cheese.
Happy to say they have the whole grilled chickens again. Back to 4 stars. Bring back the lemon parsley sauce for a fifth star!

After the renovation, this place is now a completely different restaurant.  The chicken dishes consist of pre-frozen skinned fillets instead of the juicy skin-on pieces, the French fries are burned, and the portions are ridiculously small for what you're paying.  Disregard the photos from the old reviews because they no longer apply to this business. This has now become nothing more than a one-star hole for late-night drunken munchies, a place that I predict won't stay in business for too long.  Quite a shame too because I used to look forward to making a track there across Brooklyn. Stay away~

I can't rave enough about this place. They specialize in grilled chicken, but buy, are they much more.  The decor makes me feel I'm in a wine and tapas bar.  We where fortunate enough to come when the owner (Christina) was there.  She is amazingly friendly, and made us feel right at home.  This has to be the best chicken I've ever had!  If your into Paleo or Whole 30, everything in the menu is made in-house, and it's easy to pick out what is compatible and what is not.  And those items that are not, you can customize (leave out the bread, cheese, etc.) Even salad dressing is made in-house with simple ingredients and compatible (and delicious!).

Their chicken is to die for! Me and my friends ordered the whole chicken. The chicken comes with pita bread and I wish they came us more of the bread! Was super delicious! The Mango Chutney Sauce and the Creamed Spinach Sauce is great and can be used for the chicken and the fries. The chicken is already flavorful, so it is not needed! But definitely try it with the fries! We also ordered the mac and cheese and sweet potato fries. The sweet potato fries were somewhat soggy and I wished they were crispier! The mac and cheese was so-so.  However, the people there seem to be super friendly and nice! I like how you can self-serve yourself somewhat. The place is somewhat small, but simplistic and has a nice feeling!  YOU MUST GET THE CHICKEN!

Really tasty chicken at a cozy little spot.  We came here to grab a late lunch after a show at Barclays. We ordered a chicken breast sandwich, chicken pie, and jalapeno mac n' cheese. Service was super friendly and very patient, as we took a little time to decide what we wanted.  The chicken sandwich was simple, with chicken breast, lettuce, tomato, mayo, turkey bacon, but very satisfying. I really liked the flakiness of the chicken pie and the amount of creamy chicken filling was just right. The mac n' cheese had great texture on the noodles and a nice spicy kick. The cheese was slightly less impressive, as the top of the noodles are covered in a nice thick melted cheese topping but not much cheese underneath. Still, we enjoyed everything and ate every crumb.  Special thanks to the woman at the counter who also gave me a mango dipping sauce to go with the pie. Really hit the spot!

Fantastic fantastic chicken. Half chicken satisfies two people with small to regular stomachs. Purbird sauce and mango chutney were both amazing. Licked the plate clean.... Will be my go to spot for tasty grilled chicken.

Their menu says "Home to Brooklyn's Best Flame Grilled Chicken." Actually, I believe it. The chicken is tender, moist, great char on the outside. The whole chicken is served partially deboned (breast and thigh bones removed while drumstick and wing drumette remain), and looks like it is cooked "under a brick"-style. Makes for a juicy bird with crispy skin. Chicken soup is perfect for cold winter days. Love the sides and the sauces. Modest eatery inside to grab a quick bite, but I mostly use it for take out. I have always had friendly service.

I just order a chicken salad wrap, it was not good and I was very surprised. I have ordered there before and it was always good. Today I received yesterdays lettuce sopping in dressing. Not good at all.
Awesome little restaurant for nice organic, cage free, bird meal. They just started having beer and wine, which are fine. The food is always good.

Came here with a group or 3 people. The staff was helpful in helping us decide what we wanted to eat. We ended up ordering the whole chicken, jalapeno mac and cheese, and purbird fries.  I would have to say that the food was just okay at best. The whole chicken wasn't technically a whole chicken. It didn't come with the wings. I expected a bigger chicken and more meat but the meat was quite scarce for the price you pay for a whole chicken. Definitely not worth the price point to meat ratio. However, the chicken was moist and the skin a little crisp but the meat couldn't stand on it's own flavor wise. The sauces we got were the mango chutney, lemon & parsley, and purbird sauce. Out of the 3, the best were the pubird sauce and lemon & parsley. Both were flavorful and excellent as sauces.  The fries were standard. Nothing fancy about them. You have to buy their sauces otherwise it doesn't taste that good.  The jalapeno mac and cheese was spicy and that's about it. The cheese was just okay, no special cheeses used and not much of a crisp on the top layer. Kind of soggy. Kind of tasted like Kraft's mac & cheese but spicy.  The good thing is that they have root beer!  I would not come here again nor could I recommend this place.
Finally a place where the raw ingredients are of great quality. I had a delicious chicken breast sandwich and every bit of it was wholesome. Nice to have cider and beer on tap too.

This place was very, very good. Had a chicken breast sandwich and it was excellent. During off peak times, it was a nice place to sit and talk though. Definitely want to go back :)
